Here's a playlist I have been trying to make
It's pretty small at only 6 songs at the moment but for good reason, because each and every song in this playlist symbolically represents a concept in the 2024 election that is extremely important to me.

- Freedom (Obvious)
- 365 (Enthusiasm around Harris, also pretty obvious)
- Centuries (What happens this year will be talked about for centuries for one reason or another)
- Thank You (Pushing back against backwards ideology)
- Parents (LGBTQ+ Rights)
- We won't go back (Dual meaning: Obvious / The absolutely soulless supreme court ruling that was Dobbs)

I want to expand it further if I find more songs that fit perfectly like these ones. If anyone has suggestions, let me know.

“We Can Stand Together”
By Bruce & Michelle Marshall   ©2024
"When some turn a blind eye to justice, and bury their heads in the sand;
We could squander this opportunity don't let it slip through our hands.
Now I'm feeling a sea change upon us, I ask is it pre-ordained?
If we don't take action and face all the facts, we could be forever changed.
CHORUS
We can stand together, Give our future this chance,.
Will we welcome a new world just and fair, where do you stand.
We can stand for freedom, for everyone in the land.
Our Children will carry that mantle if given the chance.
Now some say it's part of a cycle, some say it's part of a scheme;
Some say it's fate now old mother nature is coming apart at the seams.
Now most of us want all the same things, a world without bias and strife.
The same opportunity once and for all is every American's right.
CHORUS
We can stand together, Give our future this chance,.
Will we welcome a new world just and fair, where do you stand.
We can stand for freedom, for everyone in the land.
Our children will carry that mantle if given the chance.
So go blame society, go say your piece and cherish your deep held beliefs.
And all that had mattered got all torn and tattered, history always repeats.
When some turn a blind eye to justice and then quote scripture and verse;
When hypocrisy rules we call out the fools and we all take a turn for the worse.
We can stand together, Give our future this chance; 
Would we welcome a new world just and fair, where do you stand?
We can stand for freedom, for everyone in the land.
Our children will carry that mantle if given the chance.
We can stand together we can strengthen the ties.
We can't let this new found common ground get tossed by the wayside.
We can stand for freedom. We can stand for freedom."

Hi guys, 

I'd like to offer up my music for your consideration, a set of classic American tunes produced as contemporary EDM songs. 

I believe you'll find a variety of messaging that fits your campaign, from more somber songs like "A World Without Heroes" and "Waiting for the Sun" to more cheeky ones like "Rock the Nation" and "Stormtroopin". 

I want to contribute to your cause so you can use any or all of these songs as music for your ads, without any obligation (for free): 

https://soundcloud.com/makis/sets/states/s-6hrtHTOSMwe?si=2faff93ad71348698c10ed49495315b7&utm_source=clipboard&utm_medium=text&utm_campaign=social_sharing

It's late in Indiana, but I'm staying up to make sure these just-mastered-today songs get out to the world.  It's been an inspiring process writing, recording, mixing and now, releasing them in hopes everyone will spread them around.  I released "Do Something" last night.  Tonight it's "We're Not Going Back" and "He's Not Like Me and You".  I've made them all free downloads in hopes you all can share them from coast to coast.  Many thanks to everyone for your hard work.  Let's make sure we celebrate in November![    ]   https://www.reverbnation.com/philadelphiaphil/song/34676244-were-not-going-back-philadelphia
